The Jigawa State Hisbah Board has arrested one Garba Bakule with 96 bottles of alcohol and 2,125 liters of local beer (Burukutu) in Maigatari Local Government Area of ​​the state. State Hisbah Commander, Dahiru Garki, made the announcement in a statement issued to DAILY POST. He said the board will not relent on its efforts to curb the acts of social vices in the society. Garki, therefore, commended the people of the state for their support and cooperation in actualizing its mandates. He said the man was handed over to the Maigatari Police Station for investigation after which will be charged to court.